      <abstract>
        <p>Howard Goldberg reviews Jean Manciat's 2005 Macon Charnay Franclieu chardonnay wine (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Jean Manciat's 2005 Mâcon Charnay Franclieu is an appetite-sharpening chardonnay that fatigued summer visitors to southern Burgundy might dream of drinking chilled from a village fountain.</p>
        <p>Deftly tending 13.6 acres of vines in chalky soil, the organically oriented Mr. Manciat produces pure, simple, flinty chardonnay without cosmetic manipulations in his cellar.</p>
      </block>
